===Conjunction===
{{infl|en|conjunction}}

# Despite the fact that; [[although]].
#: '''''Though''' it’s risky, it’s worth taking the chance.''
# {{archaic}} [[if|If]], [[that]], [[even if]].
#: ''We be not sorry '''though''' the man dies tonight.''
#* '''1945''', [[w:Oscar Hammerstein II|Oscar Hammerstein II]], “[[w:You'll Never Walk Alone (song)|You’ll Never Walk Alone]]” (song), in [[w:Rodgers and Hammerstein|Richard Rodgers and Oscar Hammerstein II]], ''[[w:Carousel (musical)|Carousel]]'' (musical),
#*: Walk on through the wind, / Walk on through the rain, / '''Though''' your dreams be tossed and blown.

